      "ACoS = Ad Spend ÷ Ad Revenue × 100 📊\n\nBenchmarks:\n• Launch phase: 25–40% (buying rank — acceptable)\n• Growth phase: 15–25% (good)\n• Mature/profitable: 8–14% (excellent)\n\nYour break-even ACoS = your gross margin %.\nIf you make 30% margin, ACoS above 30% means you are losing money on ads.\n\n✅ EcomXprt average: we reduce client ACoS from 28% → 11%.\n\nWant help calculating your break-even ACoS?",
      "High ACoS is the most common issue we fix. 📉\n\nRoot causes we find:\n1. Broad match without negative keywords\n2. Auto campaigns never reviewed\n3. Bids too high on low-converting keywords\n4. No dayparting or placement adjustments\n\nOur fix: structured campaign architecture + weekly optimization.\nResult: 28% → 11% ACoS on average, in 60–90 days.\n\nBook a free PPC audit to see exactly where yours is leaking."
